    <note>Han(1) Zhengyan [635] Guohua's [651] grandson, Ju(1)'s [641] son, Qi(1)'s [630] and Ju(2)'s [642] nephew, Chunyan's [7031], Cuiyan's [656] and Zhongyan's [644] cousin. Wang(2) Yi(1)'s [1824] son-in-law, Wang(2) Zeng's [1901] grandson-in-law, and father-in-law of Zhang(1) Mian's [262] grandson, Yuansu [3119]. By process of elimination, Yuansu was almost certainly Zhang(1) Shen(3)'s [229] or Xun's [233] son. Yuansu was a Suzhou jinshi in 1076, and Shen(3) and Xun are the two sons of Zhang(1) Mian for whom we have no funerary inscription listing sons. The sons of both other brothers have the generational name Yuan-x. Han Qi, WJ, 48.6b-7b (wife, surname Wang, who died in 1069 at age 39); XCB, 266.2b, 335.12b, 350.7b, 402.13b, 429.9b, 431.12a, 454.6a; SHY:ZG, 66.23b; YLDD, 2368.4b. CBD, 5, 4161-2.</note>
